  "prompt": "Where can I get very traditional plastering service in Boston?",
  "response": "For traditional plastering services in Boston, you can consider the following options:\n\n1. **Local Contractors**: Many general contractors in Boston specialize in traditional plastering, especially those who focus on historic renovations. You can search for local contractors on platforms like Angie's List, HomeAdvisor, or Yelp.\n\n2. **Restoration Companies**: Look for restoration companies that specifically mention plaster work or historic restoration. They often have the expertise needed for traditional techniques.\n\n3. **Plastering Specialists**: You can find professionals who specialize in plastering through trade associations such as the Plastering & Drywall Contractors Association (PDCA) or the American College of the Building Arts.\n\n4. **Referrals**: Ask for recommendations from friends, family, or professionals in the construction and renovation industry. \n\n5. **Community Boards**: Check out local community boards or social media groups focused on home improvement in the Boston area.\n\n6. **Architectural Salvage Stores**: Sometimes, these stores have connections to skilled tradespeople who specialize in historic techniques.\n\nBe sure to check reviews, ask for portfolios of their work, and verify their experience with traditional plastering techniques before making a decision.",
